<section class="bg-stone-50 py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="container max-w-3xl text-center">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">The real problem</p>
    <h2 class="mt-4 font-serif text-3xl tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
      You're not just tired.<br />You're incorrectly dehydrated.
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-foreground/75 md:text-lg">
      Drinking water isn't enough. Your body needs minerals to absorb it — and most
      electrolyte products replace those minerals with synthetic versions your cells
      can barely use.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-16 grid gap-8 text-left sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="text-2xl">💧</div>
        <h3 class="font-medium tracking-tight">Water alone fails</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-foreground/65">
          Plain water dilutes your electrolytes instead of restoring them. The more
          you drink without minerals, the worse you can feel.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="text-2xl">🧪</div>
        <h3 class="font-medium tracking-tight">Synthetic minerals don't absorb</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-foreground/65">
          Chemically processed minerals in most supplements are poorly recognized
          by your body. You flush them out and wonder why you still feel flat.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="text-2xl">🌿</div>
        <h3 class="font-medium tracking-tight">Real minerals work differently</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-foreground/65">
          Celtic sea salt carries the full mineral spectrum your body knows how
          to use — chloride, calcium, magnesium, zinc, and more. Nature-made. Actually absorbed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
